m = n-k
\begin{align}E[N\mid K = k] &= \sum_{n\geq k}n \frac{(q\lambda)^{n-k}}{(n-k)!}e^{-q\lambda}\\ &= \sum_{m \geq 0} (m+k)\frac{(q\lambda)^{m}}{m!}e^{-q\lambda}\\ &= \sum_{m \geq 0}m\frac{(q\lambda)^{m}}{m!}e^{-q\lambda} + k \sum_{m \geq 0}\frac{(q\lambda)^{m}}{m!}e^{-q\lambda}\\ & = q\lambda + k \end{align}
